50 While we observed operational GHG reductions exceeding our 2025 goal, we recognize that in future years this may change as employees return to the office, business travel resumes and the company continues to grow.

51 Vendor climate engagement metrics are based on our assessment of all vendors within relevant Scope 3 categories, including purchased goods and services, capital goods, business travel and upstream transportation and distribution.

52 We’ve revised prior period energy and emissions metrics based on improvements in both data quality and calculation methodology. 53 Scope 2 emissions data is calculated using the GHG Protocol Market-Based Method (MBM), which includes purchases of off-site renewable energy.

54 As part of our commitment to sustainable business travel, we have worked directly with preferred travel vendors to refine our emissions calculation methodology for 2021. We will continue to work with vendors to enhance the granularity of employee travel information upon which our business travel GHG emissions calculations are based.
^ Received limited external assurance in current and/or previous reporting period.
55 Scope 2 emissions data is calculated using the GHG Protocol Market-Based Method (MBM), which includes purchases of off-site renewable energy.
56 Scope 1 emissions by facility type excluded corporate jet. 57 Calculation includes operational emissions from all Scope 1 and 2 sources, including corporate jet.
58 Water consumption data collected from facilities under PayPal’s operational control utilizing direct reporting and extrapolated data.

59 This increase was due to the shutdown of a major data center and refresh activities that occurred across our office locations. Additionally, COVID-19 significantly impacted our ability to process disposals in 2020. ^ Received limited external assurance in current and/or previous reporting period.
